OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1775782987
OL,3,CNo more 'saying no to Wales', says
OL,4,CPlaid Cymru leader at manifesto launch
OL,6,FIn Wrexham, leader Rhun ap Iorwerth
OL,7,Flaunched what he called a radical but
OL,8,Fresponsible plan for government,
OL,9,Fcentred on universal childcare from
OL,10,Fnine months, new surgical hubs to cut
OL,11,FNHS waiting lists and a promise of no
OL,12,Findependence referendum in a first
OL,13,Fterm.
OL,15,FRhun ap Iorwerth said his party would
OL,16,Fnot "bend to Westminster's will," and
OL,17,Fthere would be not be any more, as he
OL,18,Fput it, "saying no to Wales."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
