OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1775782987
OL,3,CNo more 'saying no to Wales', says
OL,4,CPlaid Cymru leader at manifesto launch
OL,6,FThe Greens also believe Wales' new
OL,7,Fproportional voting system could
OL,8,Ffinally open the door to a
OL,9,Fbreakthrough, with leader Anthony
OL,10,FSlaughter openly talking up the
OL,11,Fprospect of holding the balance of
OL,12,Fpower in a Senedd where no single
OL,13,Fparty is expected to win outright.
OL,14,FTheir headline policies include a rent-
OL,15,Ffreeze and a #1 cap on bus fares.
OL,17,FFor Labour, the challenge is defending
OL,18,Fmore than a century of dominance in
OL,19,FWales in what looks set to be its
OL,20,Ftoughest election since devolution.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
